            "reviews": "“Black Bird’s strong visual and sound direction are a callback to developer Onion Games’ previous incarnation as LOVEdeLIC, but the game itself is a hardcore shoot-'em-up. Its great design demands the player learn patterns in order to chase high scores, an approach that is enjoyable for both seasoned players and those new to the genre.”<br>85 – <a href=\"https://www.destructoid.com/review-black-bird-528112.phtml\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"  >Destructoid</a><br><br>“Black Bird is difficult, weird, and an utterly brilliant shmup you need to check out right now.”<br>80 – <a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=https://www.pocketgamer.com/articles/079092/black-bird-switch-review/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Pocket Gamer UK</a><br><br>“”<br>90 – <a href=\"https://jp.ign.com/black-bird/30038/review/black-bird\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"  >IGN Japan</a><br>",
